data.name: San Francisco Museum of Modern Art (SFMOMA)
data.description: Not just one of the largest museums in the US, SFMOMA is also one of its finest. Regularly rotating exhibits plus a hefty permanent collection, displayed on the seven floors of the striking Snøhetta expansion make this a museum well worth your time in San Francisco.

data.name: Bridge 2 Bridge Cruise
data.description: San Francisco just wouldn't be the same without the Golden Gate Bridge and the Bay Bridge giving us those picture-postcard bay-spanning views. Glide under them both and see San Francisco’s stunning skyline, complete with audio commentary on this Bridge 2 Bridge Cruise.

data.name: California Academy of Sciences
data.description: Journey from the depths of the ocean to the canopy of the jungle, and keep going all the way to the edges of the galaxy, all in one day! The California Academy of Sciences in San Francisco is the world’s only aquarium, planetarium, rainforest and natural history museum all under one incredible living roof.

data.name: San Francisco Helicopter Experience
data.description: Looking for a once-in-a-lifetime experience? Watch San Francisco get smaller and smaller the higher you go on these incredible helicopter tours. Choose from the Vista or the Vista Grande Tour (20 or 30 minutes) and see sights like the Golden Gate Bridge, Alcatraz, and Angel Island from an angle you'll never forget!

locations.address: The Fairmont Hotel, 950 Mason Street (Nob Hill)

data.name: Asian Art Museum
data.description: Explore the art and culture of all of the major regions of Asia, from Turkey to Thailand. Discover paintings, sculptures, bronzes, ceramics, and beautiful textiles. It's also home to colorful puppets, ancient gilded Buddhas, cutting-edge contemporary works, and much more.

data.name: Walt Disney Family Museum: Skip The Line
data.description: He created giant pink castles and a talking mouse that everyone seems to think is totally normal. But there's a lot more to Walt Disney that you may not know. Until you visit the Walt Disney Family Museum. Located in San Francisco's historic Presidio, this is a world of Walt's own imagining. Get to know the man behind the mouse.

data.name: Oracle Park: Guided Visit
data.description: You've really hit a home run with this ticket! Go behind the scenes of the legendary Oracle Park with a guide and see what only staff and famous baseball players usually see. Visit the Indoor Batting Cage, the Visitors' Clubhouse, a luxury suite, and more!

data.name: Silicon Valley Campus Hop
data.description: Google and Facebook might be vital parts of your life, but have you ever 'checked in' for real? Join an Incredible Adventures guide for a half or full day tour including visits to the Google Campus, Facebook, and the Computer History Museum. The full day tour also includes a drive on the stunning Pacific Coast Highway.

data.name: Yosemite Day Trip
data.description: Awe-inspiring nature and jaw-dropping scenery await when you're whisked away from San Francisco, into Yosemite National Park. Here you'll get a narrated tour, eat lunch at the base of Yosemite Falls, and enjoy 3-4 hours of hiking, biking, or just walking the trails! It's an adventure in the Great Outdoors - with an emphasis on the Great!

data.name: San Francisco Mega Pass
data.description: Save your money for Sourdough from Boudin Bakery and Irish Coffee at the Buena Vista by snapping up a Mega Pass. Build your own San Francisco Experience and choose 3, 4 or 5 options from over 25 popular attractions and tours. See SFMOMA and Madame Tussauds, jump on the Rocket Boat, take a San Francisco Bay Cruise, and much more!

data.name: 7D Experience
data.description: Lock, load, and strap in - San Francisco's 7D Experience is a ride like no other. Experience the latest virtual reality technology across four different action-packed scenarios. It's a nerve-wracking race against the clock!

data.name: San Francisco Dinner Cruise
data.description: Dining, drinking, and dancing in one of the most spectacular bays in the world – what could be better? This 4-course dinner with all-you-can-drink champagne is a 3-hour escape from the everyday into a world of luxury, glamor, and good times!

data.name: NightLife at the California Academy of Sciences
data.description: Tired of the bar scene? Trade boozers for blowfish and bullfrogs with this unique evening experience. Every Thursday, the California Academy of Sciences throws its doors open for an adults-only jamboree. Sip cocktails, explore the exhibits and get down to live music and DJs in one of the largest natural history museums in the world.

data.name: San Francisco Bike Rental
data.description: Want to see the best of San Francisco's at your own pace? Don't let the legions of lycra-clad cyclists have all the fun. Rent a trusty electric bike, a city bike, or a tandem and get ready for a freewheeling adventure of seismic proportions! Pedal your way across the all things _Golden Gate_ (bridge, park, and city!) and enjoy an epic adventure.

data.name: San Francisco Champagne Brunch Cruise
data.description: Dining, drinking, and dancing in one of the most spectacular bays in the world – what could be better? This all-you-can-eat buffet (with all-you-can-drink champagne!) is a tasty 2-hour escape from the everyday into a world of luxury, glamor, and good times!

data.name: Golden Gate Bridge: Self-Guided Bike Tour
data.description: See San Francisco the fun way on a Golden Gate Bridge self-guided bike tour. You'll get all the cycling essentials included, from camera bags to bottle holders, so go for as long as you can handle those hills!

data.name: Golden Gate Park: Guided Bike Tour
data.description: Join a guide and get the history on the 1,000-plus acre Golden Gate Park - it's a real insider's exploration! With the wind in your hair and your feet on the pedals, see Stow Lake (great for Strawberry Hill views), the sprawling Ocean Beach, Conservatory of Flowers, Shakespeare Garden and more!

data.name: Golden Gate Park: Self-Guided Bike Tour
data.description: The locals in San Francisco have been cycling around the 1,000+ acre Golden Gate Park for years. Hire a bike and explore it all on two wheels. See Stow Lake (great for Strawberry Hill views), the sprawling Ocean Beach, Conservatory of Flowers, Shakespeare Garden and more!

data.name: Surrey Bike Rental in Golden Gate Park
data.description: Saddle up and soak in the epic meadows, woodland trails and glittering lakes of Golden Gate Park on a surrey bike - the only way to travel around San Francisco's beautiful urban parkland.

locations.address: 82 Hagiwara Tea Garden Drive, Yellow & Blue Tent behind Temple of Music

data.name: Monterey Day Trip from San Francisco
data.description: Hit the road and drink in the spectacular views of the Pacific Coast on California’s iconic Highway 1. Capture jaw-dropping scenery of ocean swells and rugged cliffs along the famous _17-Mile Drive_. This day-trip from San Francisco to Monterey and Carmel will spirit you into the wild wild west, and back.

data.name: Muir Woods & Sausalito Tour from San Francisco
data.description: Get whisked over the Golden Gate bridge into the magical Muir Woods with a guide. You'll see (and hug?) giant, ancient redwood and sequoia trees - some are over 800 years old! Then it's time to explore the delightful city of Sausalito and do some shopping!

data.name: Napa Valley & Sonoma: Wine Tour from San Francisco
data.description: Red, white or rosé? Whatever your favorite wine there's bound to be something new to discover on this Napa Valley and Sonoma Wine Tour! Take a luxury coach from San Francisco for a full day's guided tour to some of the top Sonoma wineries. You'll also get a tasting at three of them!

data.name: Exploratorium: Skip The Line
data.description: San Francisco's Exploratorium is more than a museum - it's an educational experience the whole family can enjoy! Step into a world of science, art, and human perception with over 650 hands-on exhibits designed to boggle the mind.

data.name: RocketBoat on San Francisco Bay
data.description:
Is it a rocket? Is it a boat? It's someone's way of combining both, and it works! Speed your way across San Francisco Bay on this adrenaline-pumping thrill ride!

Hold on tight to your sunglasses, you're about to take off very quickly. The RocketBoat will launch you right out of your comfort zone and into something far more exciting for a whole 30 minutes!

data.name: Roundtrip Ferry from San Francisco to Angel Island
data.description:
Take the Angel Island ferry and spend some time at one of the Bay Area's most interesting historic sites. Check out the military garrisons, visit the newly-restored Immigration Station, and get amazing views of the San Francisco skyline.

The views from Angel Island, also known as the 'Ellis Island of the West', are some of the best around! Soak up the expansive 360° panoramas of the San Francisco skyline, the Marin Headlands, and Mount Tamalpais.

data.name: Escape from the Rock: Bay Cruise
data.description: Wear something warm, because you might get goosebumps listening to tales of this prison's dark and creepy history. From escape attempts to infamous inmates, to legends of ghosts and hauntings, Alcatraz has it all! Bring your own phone and get ready to plug into a chilling slice of American history on the _Escape from the Rock_ cruise.

data.name: Exploratorium After Dark Thursdays: Skip The Line
data.description: San Francisco's Exploratorium is more than just a fun and educational museum during daytime - it's a lot of fun on Thursday nights, too. Step into a world of science, art, and human perception at night with over 650 hands-on exhibits designed to boggle the mind.

data.name: Aquarium of the Bay
data.description: If you're going to San Francisco, be sure to visit the Aquarium of the Bay. Located at Pier 39, this aquarium has 20,000 local sea creatures ready for seeing and even touching. With a 300-foot underwater tunnel, nature talks, and thousands of sea creatures, this is an amazing - and interactive - way to get to know the waters that surround this city.

data.name: Pier 39 Attraction Pass
data.description: Pier 39 is an unmissable part of San Francisco, thanks in part to the lively sea lions on the K-Dock. They're a must-see, but this waterside area is also home to many more fun-filled attractions. Visit the Aquarium of the Bay, take a relaxing Bay Cruise, ride the Hop-on Hop-off bus, feel the thrill of a 7D Experience, and get lost in Magowan’s Mirror Maze. All with this one easy pass!

data.name: San Francisco Bay Cruise
data.description: San Fran may be a tech hub, but you didn't come here to watch bearded guys work in open plan offices. Besides, San Francisco is home to world-class sights like the majestic Golden Gate Bridge and eerie Alcatraz Island. You'll see both these highlights and more when you take to the water for this San Francisco Bay Cruise, complete with audio guide.

data.name: San Francisco Sunset Cruise
data.description: As the sun sets over the Pacific Ocean the water shimmers in different colors and the San Francisco highlights have a special kind of glow. On this 2-hour sunset cruise you'll enjoy delicious appetizers as you're serenaded by live guitar music. Cruise past the Golden Gate Bridge, Sausalito, Tiburon, Angel Island and Alcatraz in style!

data.name: Hop-On Hop-Off Bus San Francisco
data.description: Hop on a double-decker open-topped bus with a fun guide, and cruise the hills and streets of San Francisco! Enjoy up to four tours, with more than 32 stops (throughout San Francisco and Sausalito). As a bonus, get three different walking tours and one hour on a bike rental. Don't just go to San Francisco - _experience_ the city!

data.name: de Young Museum
data.description: Spend some time getting up to scratch with your art here at the de Young, which strives to stay involved in today's most relevant cultural discussions. Be inspired by American art from the 17th to 21st centuries, international contemporary art, textiles, costumes and more!

data.name: GoCar San Francisco
data.description: If zipping around San Francisco in a little yellow car sounds fun, that’s because it really is. Get your helmet on, choose your route, and let the onboard GPS system on this souped-up go-kart guide you along the way. Forget about streetcars, there’s a GoCar named desire waiting for you.
